Two hours of ambient and dreamy downtempo compositions from Dearborn, Michigan husband-and-wife duo Windy & Carl. Eschewing the more commonly used synthesizers popular with other ambient artists, the duo generate their shimering soundscapes predominantly stem from guitar and bass, with effects, e-bows and more.
Bimonthly radio hour taking you down various musical rabbit holes.

The Blackest Ever Black released singer-songwriter Carla Dal Forno stops by NTS' London studio once a month for an hour-long show featuring original productions side by side with old favourites and inspirations ranging from minimal synth to folk and dream pop…

"It is not easy to find Saphira, and it is even harder to leave. Saphira is caught between a low-lying sun to the west and a glowing moon to the east, Saphira’s longing grows dense and time thickens within its walls. Perhaps this is why Saphira’s radios and televisions stutter with phrases and images so ghostly yet so intimately familiar, why its dusty buildings seem always to crumble so gloriously yet never collapse. It is a city inside of want and outside of time."
Rising Dutch producer + DJ Upsammy brings her ear for crystalline melody and intricate rhythm to the NTS airwaves for adventurous and narrative mixes once a month.

nts2.n: CULTIVATION OF MIND W/ BAMBOY - SANT VANI SPECIAL (R)
nts2.d:
Cultivation of Mind celebrates India's diverse musical landscapes, focusing on the artistry of lower caste and tribal communities. The show explores how their music tells stories, builds identity, and embodies resistance, blending traditional melodies with modern elements. 
Join us as we explore the rich tapestry of India’s musical heritage, where every note carries a story worth hearing.

nts2.n: AN IBEX BAND SPECIAL: THE ROHA BAND YEARS (R)
nts2.d:
The legendary Ibex Band - later known as the iconic Roha Band - played a key role in shaping Ethiopian music from the mid-1970s onward. Though hugely influential, their legacy remains underrecognised. In this special episode, NTS presents a two hour deep dive into their catalogue, tracing their evolution and showcasing rare, overlooked tracks from their archive. Join us as we celebrate the musicians behind the music and explore their lasting cultural impact. 
Special thanks to John Henriksson, Johan Egerbladh Eurenius, Muzikawi and Zuret Addis.
Image courtesy of Selam Seyoum Woldemariam.

subtle.d: Japanese DJ from Tokyo, currently living in London.  Based on UK club music, but straddles other genres such as dancehall, reggaeton, gqom and amapiano.

Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".

Kishan is a DJ and Producer currently based in London. Actively involved in the music scene already, he produces and mixes a wide range of genres including UK Garage, Drum & Bass, House, Disco and Afrobeat.

Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy
